instructions:
Build a cross-platform parity matrix for the four quickstart pages. Known signal: line counts diverge sharply (android 346, ios 240, web 143, flutter 80) which suggests significant content gaps.

Steps:

1. Read each of the four context files. Extract the section structure (H2 and H3 headings) and the key concepts covered in each section.
2. Build a unified section taxonomy across all four pages. Pick the most-complete page as the structural template (likely android given its length, but verify by inspection).
3. For each (section, platform) cell, mark: 'present' / 'partial' / 'missing' / 'n_a' (n_a only when the section genuinely does not apply to the platform — e.g. a 'CocoaPods' section is iOS-only).
4. For each gap cell, draft a one-sentence description of what content needs to be added, and assign a tier (A/B/C per rubric.json):
   - Tier A: stub generation from SDK README / SDK source / sibling page (mechanical).
   - Tier B: needs platform-idiomatic example code (AI can draft from SDK, human rubber-stamps).
   - Tier C: genuinely platform-specific guidance only an expert can write.
5. Write the matrix to `.docs-ops/evals/parity-matrix-quickstarts.json` with this shape:
   {
     "generated_at": "<iso>",
     "generated_by": "<agent_id>",
     "template_page": "<repo-relative path>",
     "template_rationale": "<one sentence>",
     "sections": [
       {
         "section": "<unified heading>",
         "cells": {
           "ios":     { "status": "present|partial|missing|n_a", "gap_description": "<sentence if not present>", "tier": "A|B|C|null" },
           "android": { ... },
           "flutter": { ... },
           "web":     { ... }
         }
       }
     ],
     "summary": {
       "total_gaps": <int>,
       "by_tier": { "A": <int>, "B": <int>, "C": <int> }
     }
   }
6. For each Tier A gap, generate a follow-up task file in `.docs-ops/tasks/pending/` (id starting from `0004-`). Each follow-up task should target a single page and a single gap so it stays under 5 min of agent work.
7. Do NOT edit the four quickstart pages themselves in this task.

Report the gap summary in the result's `notes` field. List the ids of all follow-up tasks created in `follow_up_tasks`.
